value.0: The Barkeep, Fendel. You notice that he is usually stroking his beard when he is not serving someone, and tends to wink at his customers after serving them.  There is a tattoo on his left arm that has the word "NO" written in big letters.
The Book of Brandobaris, which loves to play 'hide and seek' or 'catch me if you can' more than anything else.
The mouse eyes you suspiciously as you move around in the cellar.

The Bendir Dale Militia, these hin appear to be geared for proper combat, with masks carefully hiding their faces, making them seem alike.  Their eyes are very observant and tend to squint towards you if you observe them too much.
Armor of the battle hins in Bendir Dale.
A Fresh-faced gnome with muffin crumbs on his shirt
A little man made of gingerbread that looks good enough to eat! That is, until it looks back at you...
A little man made of gingerbread that looks good enough to eat! ...Wait, why isn't this one moving like the rest of them? AND WHERE DID IT'S HEAD GO!?

Various notices are tacked up on the board.
A carefully constructed marker denoting a point of interest.
A carefully constructed marker denoting a point of interest.
You better hope its not meant for you, as this present will be nothing you want to get.
Various top secret plans, schemes and pranks.
This is an angry little silver cup, which bites anyone who tries to drink from it!
Best not to attempt to make sense of this chaotic and sinister plan, what ever it may be.
Why is this fire blue you ask? Better not to know, or eat anything cooked with it.
No wonder why they are so creative!

Dogma of Cyrrollalee: Be generous in friendship, and welcome all friends into your home and trust. Never betray the trust of a host, break an oath, or violate the sanctity of another's home. The Day of Discovery approaches, when all hin rally around a new home based upon dignity, companionship, and love.
